cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper is about a novel distributed training framework for recommender systems, which involves machine learning (ML) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale dynamic sparse features, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents an implementation that outperforms state-of-the-art recommender systems, which indicates that it may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
